🎗️ BROWSER
URL - Uniform Resource Locator
📌 URL FORMAT :
          schema://domain:port/query_string#fragment_id
Example : https://www.geeksforgeeks.org


📌 Several parts of URL : 
✔️ Schema or Protocol - http,https,ftp.....
✔️ Sever domain name - .edu , .com , .org ,....
✔️ Port(default : 80) - Optional
✔️ Path to resource with name & extension - .html....
✔️ Query string - optional
✔️ Fragmet Id - optional


📌 WORKING : 
The url will perform GET URL to the DOMAIN NAME 
and it request the resource which is given in the url 
then the resource is return back to the client browser and
the resource is displayed.

HTML contains - Contents , Structures and URL's
✔️ Media - Content
✔️ Stylesheet - Appearance
✔️ JavaScript - Behaviour
Internal Data Structures publish - Document Object Model(DOM)



🎗️DOCUMENT OBJECT MODEL (DOM)

✔️ Document - file
✔️ Object - tagelements
✔️ Model - layer structure 

✔️ DOM represents the content of an XML or HTML document as a tree structure.
✔️ Programming interface or an API.
✔️ Easily read,access and update the content of the document.
✔️ Object-Oriented representation of the web page.It can be modified with a scripting languages such as javascript.


✔️ All HTML elements can be accessed through the XML DOM.

📌 MARKUP TEST : 

<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<meta charset="utf-8">
<title>Page Title</title>
<body>
   <h1>This is a Heading</h1>
   <p>This is a paragraph.</p>
   <p>This is another paragraph.</p>
</body>
</html>


📌 DOCUMENT OBJECT MODEL (DOM) :

|-DOCTYPE: html
|-HTML lang="en"
 |--HEAD
 | |----META charset="utf-8"
 | |----#text:
 | |----TITLE
 | |------#text: Page Title
 | |----#text:
 |-BODY
   |--#text:
   |--H1
   | |----#text: This is a Heading
   |--#text:
   |--P
   | |----#text: This is a paragraph.
   |--#text:
   |--P
   | |----#text: This is another paragraph.
   |--#text:
